<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-07-30T19:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-07-30T19:36:00-05:00" n="1132" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1132">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/4522.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Ambassador</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-07-30T18:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 30, 1912—6 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>In accordance with your July 29, 4 p.m., I have forwarded your July 28,
                            midnight, to the Consul at Chihuahua, and added following: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                <p>The Department subsequently instructed the Embassy to instruct
                                    you to do all you can to alleviate conditions and to send
                                    Department your recommendations as soon as possible. The
                                    authority lodged in you hereby should be used <pb facs="0940" n="824" xml:id="pg_824"/> without hesitation if conditions
                                    exist with you similar to those reported by Consul Edwards. When
                                    and where necessary act on Department’s March 2, 2 p.m.</p>
                            </quote>
                        </p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Wilson.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>